How to use 'update.sh'

Examples:
When you create git repository of cure, type the following:
 $ ./update.sh cure-1.0.0-beta3

When you upgrade cure to ver. 1.0.0-beta4, type the following:
 $ ./update.sh cure-1.0.0-beta4

If you want to disable automatic commit, type the following:
 $ AUTO_COMMIT=n ./update.sh cure-1.0.0-beta4

When you upgrade to the latest version, type the following:
 $ tail -n 1 versions/cure | xargs -n 1 ./update.sh

When you create all the commit history, type the following:
 $ cat versions/cure | xargs -n 1 ./update.sh
